{"sn1.60":{"sn1.60:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.60 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.60 ","html":"<article id='sn1.60'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.60:0.2":{"pli":"6. Jarāvagga ","eng":"6. Old Age ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.60:0.3":{"pli":"Kavisutta ","eng":"A Poet ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.60:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu nidānaṃ gāthānaṃ, ","eng":"“What’s the source of verses? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"In this short discourse the Buddha articulates a naturalistic theory of poetry. "},"sn1.60:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu tāsaṃ viyañjanaṃ; ","eng":"What constitutes their phrasing? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.60:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu sannissitā gāthā, ","eng":"What do verses depend upon? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.60:1.4":{"pli":"kiṃsu gāthānamāsayo”ti. ","eng":"What underlies verses?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.60:2.1":{"pli":"“Chando nidānaṃ gāthānaṃ, ","eng":"“Metre is the source of verses. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Rig Veda 10.90.9 says that verses, chants, and metres were born, rather, from the sacrifice. "},"sn1.60:2.2":{"pli":"akkharā tāsaṃ viyañjanaṃ; ","eng":"Syllables constitute their phrasing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The <i lang='pi' translate='no'>akkhara</i> (“syllable”) is the smallest indivisible morpheme, typically consisting of a consonant bound with a vowel. Mystically, it is the “imperishable” Divinity within all things. The “phrasing” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>viyañjana</i>) is the complex linguistic expression. Verses and other expressions are often counted by their syllables (eg. Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 6.2.1.22, 6.2.2.33,  6.3.1.43). "},"sn1.60:2.3":{"pli":"Nāmasannissitā gāthā, ","eng":"Verses depend on names. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Chāndogya Upaniṣad 7.1.4 defines “name” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>nāma</i>) as the Vedic texts and sciences. "},"sn1.60:2.4":{"pli":"kavi gāthānamāsayo”ti. ","eng":"A poet underlies verses.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>","comm":"The Buddha uses the worldly word for “poet” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>kavi</i>) instead of the divinely-inspired Vedic “seer” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>isi</i>). "},"sn1.60:2.5":{"pli":"Jarāvaggo chaṭṭho. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p>"},"sn1.60:3.0":{"pli":"Tassuddānaṃ ","html":"<p class='uddana-intro'>{}</p>"},"sn1.60:3.1":{"pli":"Jarā ajarasā mittaṃ, ","html":"<blockquote class='uddanagatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.60:3.2":{"pli":"vatthu tīṇi janāni ca; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.60:3.3":{"pli":"Uppatho ca dutiyo ca, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.60:3.4":{"pli":"kavinā pūrito vaggoti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.61":{"sn1.61:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.61 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.61 ","html":"<article id='sn1.61'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.61:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.61:0.3":{"pli":"Nāmasutta ","eng":"Name ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.61:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu sabbaṃ addhabhavi, ","eng":"“What overcomes everything? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.61:1.2":{"pli":"kismā bhiyyo na vijjati; ","eng":"What is it that nothing excels? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.61:1.3":{"pli":"Kissassu ekadhammassa, ","eng":"What is the one thing ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.61:1.4":{"pli":"sabbeva vasamanvagū”ti. ","eng":"that has everything under its sway?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.61:2.1":{"pli":"“Nāmaṃ sabbaṃ addhabhavi, ","eng":"“Name overcomes everything. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Compare Kauṣītaki Brāhmaṇa 20.2.32, Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 4.6.5.3. "},"sn1.61:2.2":{"pli":"nāmā bhiyyo na vijjati; ","eng":"Nothing excels name. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"This contradicts Chāndogya Upaniṣad 7.1.5, which states, “Surely there is that which excels name” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>nāmno vāva bhūyo ’stīti</i>), which it says is the “speech” that makes the scripture known. "},"sn1.61:2.3":{"pli":"Nāmassa ekadhammassa, ","eng":"Name is the one thing ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.61:2.4":{"pli":"sabbeva vasamanvagū”ti. ","eng":"that has everything under its sway.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>","comm":"The Buddha is refuting the doctrine that “name” (and form) come to an end in the ocean of infinite consciousness (see too <a href='index.html?q=dn15#22.6'>DN 15:22.6</a>). "}},"sn1.62":{"sn1.62:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.62 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.62 ","html":"<article id='sn1.62'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.62:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.62:0.3":{"pli":"Cittasutta ","eng":"Mind ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.62:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassu nīyati loko, ","eng":"“What leads the world on? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.62:1.2":{"pli":"kenassu parikassati; ","eng":"What drags it around? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.62:1.3":{"pli":"Kissassu ekadhammassa, ","eng":"What is the one thing ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.62:1.4":{"pli":"sabbeva vasamanvagū”ti. ","eng":"that has everything under its sway?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.62:2.1":{"pli":"“Cittena nīyati loko, ","eng":"“The mind leads the world on. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.62:2.2":{"pli":"cittena parikassati; ","eng":"The mind drags it around. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.62:2.3":{"pli":"Cittassa ekadhammassa, ","eng":"Mind is the one thing ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.62:2.4":{"pli":"sabbeva vasamanvagū”ti. ","eng":"that has everything under its sway.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.63":{"sn1.63:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.63 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.63 ","html":"<article id='sn1.63'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.63:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.63:0.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāsutta ","eng":"Craving ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.63:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassu nīyati loko, ","eng":"“What leads the world on? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.63:1.2":{"pli":"kenassu parikassati; ","eng":"What drags it around? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.63:1.3":{"pli":"Kissassu ekadhammassa, ","eng":"What is the one thing ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.63:1.4":{"pli":"sabbeva vasamanvagū”ti. ","eng":"that has everything under its sway?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.63:2.1":{"pli":"“Taṇhāya nīyati loko, ","eng":"“Craving leads the world on. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.63:2.2":{"pli":"taṇhāya parikassati; ","eng":"Craving drags it around. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.63:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāya ekadhammassa, ","eng":"Craving is the one thing ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.63:2.4":{"pli":"sabbeva vasamanvagū”ti. ","eng":"that has everything under its sway.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.64":{"sn1.64:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.64 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.64 ","html":"<article id='sn1.64'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.64:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.64:0.3":{"pli":"Saṃyojanasutta ","eng":"Fetter ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.64:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu saṃyojano loko, ","eng":"“What fetters the world? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.64:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu tassa vicāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"How does it travel about? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The commentary here explains <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vicāraṇa</i> as “feet”. "},"sn1.64:1.3":{"pli":"Kissassu vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of what ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.64:1.4":{"pli":"nibbānaṃ iti vuccatī”ti. ","eng":"is extinguishment spoken of?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.64:2.1":{"pli":"“Nandīsaṃyojano loko, ","eng":"“Delight fetters the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.64:2.2":{"pli":"vitakkassa vicāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"It travels about by means of thought. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.64:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāya vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of craving ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.64:2.4":{"pli":"nibbānaṃ iti vuccatī”ti. ","eng":"extinguishment is spoken of.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.65":{"sn1.65:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.65 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.65 ","html":"<article id='sn1.65'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.65:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.65:0.3":{"pli":"Bandhanasutta ","eng":"Bonds ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.65:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu sambandhano loko, ","eng":"“What binds the world? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.65:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu tassa vicāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"How does it travel about? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.65:1.3":{"pli":"Kissassu vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of what ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.65:1.4":{"pli":"sabbaṃ chindati bandhanan”ti. ","eng":"are all bonds severed?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.65:2.1":{"pli":"“Nandīsambandhano loko, ","eng":"“Delight binds the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.65:2.2":{"pli":"vitakkassa vicāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"It travels about by means of thought. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.65:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāya vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of craving ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.65:2.4":{"pli":"sabbaṃ chindati bandhanan”ti. ","eng":"all bonds are severed.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.66":{"sn1.66:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.66 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.66 ","html":"<article id='sn1.66'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.66:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.66:0.3":{"pli":"Attahatasutta ","eng":"Beaten Down ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.66:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassubbhāhato loko, ","eng":"“By what is the world beaten down? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.66:1.2":{"pli":"kenassu parivārito; ","eng":"By what is it surrounded? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.66:1.3":{"pli":"Kena sallena otiṇṇo, ","eng":"What dart has laid it low? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.66:1.4":{"pli":"kissa dhūpāyito sadā”ti. ","eng":"With what is it always fuming?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.66:2.1":{"pli":"“Maccunābbhāhato loko, ","eng":"“The world is beaten down by death. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.66:2.2":{"pli":"jarāya parivārito; ","eng":"It’s surrounded by old age. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.66:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāsallena otiṇṇo, ","eng":"The dart of craving has laid it low. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.66:2.4":{"pli":"icchādhūpāyito sadā”ti. ","eng":"It’s always fuming with desire.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.67":{"sn1.67:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.67 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.67 ","html":"<article id='sn1.67'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.67:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.67:0.3":{"pli":"Uḍḍitasutta ","eng":"Ensnared ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.67:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassu uḍḍito loko, ","eng":"“By what is the world ensnared? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.67:1.2":{"pli":"kenassu parivārito; ","eng":"By what is it surrounded? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.67:1.3":{"pli":"Kenassu pihito loko, ","eng":"By what is the world fastened shut? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.67:1.4":{"pli":"kismiṃ loko patiṭṭhito”ti. ","eng":"On what is the world grounded?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.67:2.1":{"pli":"“Taṇhāya uḍḍito loko, ","eng":"“Craving has ensnared the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.67:2.2":{"pli":"jarāya parivārito; ","eng":"It’s surrounded by old age. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.67:2.3":{"pli":"Maccunā pihito loko, ","eng":"The world is fastened shut by mortality. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.67:2.4":{"pli":"dukkhe loko patiṭṭhito”ti. ","eng":"The world is grounded on suffering.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.68":{"sn1.68:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.68 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.68 ","html":"<article id='sn1.68'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.68:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.68:0.3":{"pli":"Pihitasutta ","eng":"Fastened Shut ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.68:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassu pihito loko, ","eng":"“By what is the world fastened shut? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"This is the same as the previous, except the lines are rearranged. "},"sn1.68:1.2":{"pli":"kismiṃ loko patiṭṭhito; ","eng":"On what is the world grounded? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.68:1.3":{"pli":"Kenassu uḍḍito loko, ","eng":"By what is the world ensnared? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.68:1.4":{"pli":"kenassu parivārito”ti. ","eng":"By what is it surrounded?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.68:2.1":{"pli":"“Maccunā pihito loko, ","eng":"“The world is fastened shut by mortality. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.68:2.2":{"pli":"dukkhe loko patiṭṭhito; ","eng":"The world is grounded on suffering. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.68:2.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāya uḍḍito loko, ","eng":"Craving has ensnared the world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.68:2.4":{"pli":"jarāya parivārito”ti. ","eng":"It’s surrounded by old age.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.69":{"sn1.69:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.69 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.69 ","html":"<article id='sn1.69'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.69:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.69:0.3":{"pli":"Icchāsutta ","eng":"Desire ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.69:1.1":{"pli":"“Kenassu bajjhatī loko, ","eng":"“What is it that binds the world? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.69:1.2":{"pli":"kissa vinayāya muccati; ","eng":"By removing what is it freed? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.69:1.3":{"pli":"Kissassu vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of what ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.69:1.4":{"pli":"sabbaṃ chindati bandhanan”ti. ","eng":"are all bonds severed?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.69:2.1":{"pli":"“Icchāya bajjhatī loko, ","eng":"“Desire is what binds the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.69:2.2":{"pli":"icchāvinayāya muccati; ","eng":"By the removing of desire it’s freed. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.69:2.3":{"pli":"Icchāya vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.69:2.4":{"pli":"sabbaṃ chindati bandhanan”ti. ","eng":"all bonds are severed.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.7":{"sn1.7:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.7 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.7 ","html":"<article id='sn1.7'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.7:0.2":{"pli":"1. Naḷavagga ","eng":"1. A Reed ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.7:0.3":{"pli":"Appaṭividitasutta ","eng":"Not Comprehending ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.7:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn1.7:1.2":{"pli":"Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ","eng":"Standing to one side, that deity spoke this verse in the Buddha’s presence: ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn1.7:2.1":{"pli":"“Yesaṃ dhammā appaṭividitā, ","eng":"“Those have not deciphered the teachings ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Paṭividita</i> (“deciphered”) is found only here and <a href='index.html?q=dn1#1.3.2'>DN 1:1.3.2</a>, where it is likewise in the context of understanding views. "},"sn1.7:2.2":{"pli":"Paravādesu nīyare; ","eng":"may be led astray by the doctrines of others. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.7:2.3":{"pli":"Suttā te nappabujjhanti, ","eng":"Asleep, they have not woken up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.7:2.4":{"pli":"Kālo tesaṃ pabujjhitun”ti. ","eng":"it is time for them to wake!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.7:3.1":{"pli":"“Yesaṃ dhammā suppaṭividitā, ","eng":"“Those who have well deciphered the teachings ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.7:3.2":{"pli":"Paravādesu na nīyare; ","eng":"won’t be led astray by the doctrines of others. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.7:3.3":{"pli":"Te sambuddhā sammadaññā, ","eng":"They have woken up, they rightly know, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.7:3.4":{"pli":"Caranti visame saman”ti. ","eng":"smoothly they walk in the rough.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.70":{"sn1.70:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.70 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.70 ","html":"<article id='sn1.70'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.70:0.2":{"pli":"7. Addhavagga ","eng":"7. Overcome ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.70:0.3":{"pli":"Lokasutta ","eng":"The World ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.70:1.1":{"pli":"“Kismiṃ loko samuppanno, ","eng":"“In what has the world arisen? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:1.2":{"pli":"kismiṃ kubbati santhavaṃ; ","eng":"With what does it get intimate? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:1.3":{"pli":"Kissa loko upādāya, ","eng":"By grasping what ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"I follow Bodhi’s construal of these lines, see note 126 in <em>Connected Discourses</em>. "},"sn1.70:1.4":{"pli":"kismiṃ loko vihaññatī”ti. ","eng":"is the world troubled in what?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.70:2.1":{"pli":"“Chasu loko samuppanno, ","eng":"“The world has arisen in six. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The six senses. "},"sn1.70:2.2":{"pli":"chasu kubbati santhavaṃ; ","eng":"It gets intimate with six. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:2.3":{"pli":"Channameva upādāya, ","eng":"Derived from the six, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:2.4":{"pli":"chasu loko vihaññatī”ti. ","eng":"the world’s troubled in six.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"sn1.70:2.5":{"pli":"Addhavaggo sattamo. ","html":"<p class='endvagga'>{}</p>"},"sn1.70:3.0":{"pli":"Tassuddānaṃ ","html":"<p class='uddana-intro'>{}</p>"},"sn1.70:3.1":{"pli":"Nāmaṃ cittañca taṇhā ca, ","html":"<blockquote class='uddanagatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:3.2":{"pli":"saṃyojanañca bandhanā; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:3.3":{"pli":"Abbhāhatuḍḍito pihito, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.70:3.4":{"pli":"icchā lokena te dasāti. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.71":{"sn1.71:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.71 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.71 ","html":"<article id='sn1.71'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.71:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.71:0.3":{"pli":"Chetvāsutta ","eng":"Slain ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.71:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn1.71:1.2":{"pli":"Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ","eng":"Standing to one side, that deity addressed the Buddha in verse: ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn1.71:2.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu chetvā sukhaṃ seti, ","eng":"“When what is slain do you sleep at ease? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"For reading <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jhatvā</i> with the primary sense “to slay”, see Brough, <em>The Gāndhārī Dharmapada</em>, p. 265, note on verses 288, 289. "},"sn1.71:2.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu chetvā na socati; ","eng":"When what is slain is there no sorrow? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:2.3":{"pli":"Kissassu ekadhammassa, ","eng":"What’s the one thing, Gotama, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:2.4":{"pli":"vadhaṃ rocesi gotamā”ti. ","eng":"whose killing you approve?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.71:3.1":{"pli":"“Kodhaṃ chetvā sukhaṃ seti, ","eng":"“When anger’s slain you sleep at ease. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:3.2":{"pli":"kodhaṃ chetvā na socati; ","eng":"When anger’s slain there is no sorrow. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:3.3":{"pli":"Kodhassa visamūlassa, ","eng":"O deity, anger has a poisonous root ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:3.4":{"pli":"madhuraggassa devate; ","eng":"and a honey tip. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:3.5":{"pli":"Vadhaṃ ariyā pasaṃsanti, ","eng":"The noble ones praise its killing, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.71:3.6":{"pli":"tañhi chetvā na socatī”ti. ","eng":"for when it’s slain there is no sorrow.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.72":{"sn1.72:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.72 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.72 ","html":"<article id='sn1.72'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.72:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.72:0.3":{"pli":"Rathasutta ","eng":"A Chariot ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.72:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu rathassa paññāṇaṃ, ","eng":"“What is a chariot known by? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.72:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu paññāṇamaggino; ","eng":"What is fire known by? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.72:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu raṭṭhassa paññāṇaṃ, ","eng":"What is a nation known by? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.72:1.4":{"pli":"kiṃsu paññāṇamitthiyā”ti. ","eng":"What is a woman known by?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.72:2.1":{"pli":"“Dhajo rathassa paññāṇaṃ, ","eng":"“A chariot is known by a banner. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.72:2.2":{"pli":"dhūmo paññāṇamaggino; ","eng":"Fire is known by smoke. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.72:2.3":{"pli":"Rājā raṭṭhassa paññāṇaṃ, ","eng":"A nation is known by its ruler. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.72:2.4":{"pli":"bhattā paññāṇamitthiyā”ti. ","eng":"A woman is known by her husband.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.73":{"sn1.73:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.73 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.73 ","html":"<article id='sn1.73'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.73:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.73:0.3":{"pli":"Vittasutta ","eng":"Wealth ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.73:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsūdha vittaṃ purisassa seṭṭhaṃ, ","eng":"“What’s a person’s best wealth? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.73:1.2":{"pli":"Kiṃsu suciṇṇo sukhamāvahati; ","eng":"What brings happiness when practiced well? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.73:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu have sādutaraṃ rasānaṃ, ","eng":"What’s the sweetest taste of all? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.73:1.4":{"pli":"Kathaṃjīviṃ jīvitamāhu seṭṭhan”ti. ","eng":"The one they say has the best life: how do they live?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.73:2.1":{"pli":"“Saddhīdha vittaṃ purisassa seṭṭhaṃ, ","eng":"“Faith here is a person’s best wealth. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.73:2.2":{"pli":"Dhammo suciṇṇo sukhamāvahati; ","eng":"The teaching brings happiness when practiced well. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.73:2.3":{"pli":"Saccaṃ have sādutaraṃ rasānaṃ, ","eng":"Truth is the sweetest taste of all. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.73:2.4":{"pli":"Paññājīviṃ jīvitamāhu seṭṭhan”ti. ","eng":"The one they say has the best life lives by wisdom.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.74":{"sn1.74:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.74 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.74 ","html":"<article id='sn1.74'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.74:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.74:0.3":{"pli":"Vuṭṭhisutta ","eng":"Rain ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.74:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu uppatataṃ seṭṭhaṃ, ","eng":"“What’s the best of things that rise? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu nipatataṃ varaṃ; ","eng":"And what’s the finest thing to fall? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu pavajamānānaṃ, ","eng":"And what of the things that go forth? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:1.4":{"pli":"kiṃsu pavadataṃ varan”ti. ","eng":"And who’s the finest speaker?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.74:2.1":{"pli":"“Bījaṃ uppatataṃ seṭṭhaṃ, ","eng":"“A seed’s the best of things that rise. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:2.2":{"pli":"vuṭṭhi nipatataṃ varā; ","eng":"Rain’s the finest thing to fall. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:2.3":{"pli":"Gāvo pavajamānānaṃ, ","eng":"Cattle, of things that go forth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:2.4":{"pli":"putto pavadataṃ varo”ti. ","eng":"And a child is the finest speaker.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"The commentary says this refers to a child who testifies on one’s behalf in a court of law. But I think it is about the joy a parent feels when they hear their child speak for the first time. Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 7.4.2.38 says, “children utter speech” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>prajā vācam pravadanti</i>) when one year old. "},"sn1.74:3.1":{"pli":"“Vijjā uppatataṃ seṭṭhā, ","eng":"“Knowledge is best of things that rise. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:3.2":{"pli":"avijjā nipatataṃ varā; ","eng":"Ignorance the finest thing to fall. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:3.3":{"pli":"Saṅgho pavajamānānaṃ, ","eng":"The Saṅgha, of things that go forth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.74:3.4":{"pli":"buddho pavadataṃ varo”ti. ","eng":"And the Buddha is the finest speaker.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.75":{"sn1.75:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.75 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.75 ","html":"<article id='sn1.75'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.75:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.75:0.3":{"pli":"Bhītāsutta ","eng":"Afraid ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.75:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsūdha bhītā janatā anekā, ","eng":"“Why are so many people here afraid, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:1.2":{"pli":"Maggo canekāyatanappavutto; ","eng":"when the path has been taught <j>with so many dimensions? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:1.3":{"pli":"Pucchāmi taṃ gotama bhūripañña, ","eng":"I ask you, Gotama, whose wisdom is vast: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:1.4":{"pli":"Kismiṃ ṭhito paralokaṃ na bhāye”ti. ","eng":"Standing on what need one not fear the next world?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.75:2.1":{"pli":"“Vācaṃ manañca paṇidhāya sammā, ","eng":"“When speech and mind are directed right, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:2.2":{"pli":"Kāyena pāpāni akubbamāno; ","eng":"and you don’t do anything bad with the body ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:2.3":{"pli":"Bahvannapānaṃ gharamāvasanto, ","eng":"while dwelling at home with plenty of food and drink. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:2.4":{"pli":"Saddho mudū saṃvibhāgī vadaññū; ","eng":"Faithful, gentle, charitable, and bountiful: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:2.5":{"pli":"Etesu dhammesu ṭhito catūsu, ","eng":"one who stands on these four principles, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.75:2.6":{"pli":"Dhamme ṭhito paralokaṃ na bhāye”ti. ","eng":"who stands on the teaching <j>need not fear the next world.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.76":{"sn1.76:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.76 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.76 ","html":"<article id='sn1.76'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.76:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.76:0.3":{"pli":"Najīratisutta ","eng":"Getting Old ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.76:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃ jīrati kiṃ na jīrati, ","eng":"“What ages, what does not age? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu uppathoti vuccati; ","eng":"What’s called a deviation? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu dhammānaṃ paripantho, ","eng":"What’s a roadblock for skillful qualities? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:1.4":{"pli":"kiṃsu rattindivakkhayo; ","eng":"What is ending day and night? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:1.5":{"pli":"Kiṃ malaṃ brahmacariyassa, ","eng":"What’s the stain of celibacy? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:1.6":{"pli":"kiṃ sinānamanodakaṃ. ","eng":"What’s the waterless bath? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.76:2.1":{"pli":"Kati lokasmiṃ chiddāni, ","eng":"How many holes are there in the world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:2.2":{"pli":"yattha vittaṃ na tiṭṭhati; ","eng":"where one’s wealth leaks out? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:2.3":{"pli":"Bhagavantaṃ puṭṭhumāgamma, ","eng":"We’ve come to ask you, worthy sir: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:2.4":{"pli":"kathaṃ jānemu taṃ mayan”ti. ","eng":"how are we to understand this?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.76:3.1":{"pli":"“Rūpaṃ jīrati maccānaṃ, ","eng":"“The physical form of mortals gets old, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:3.2":{"pli":"nāmagottaṃ na jīrati; ","eng":"but their name and clan don’t. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:3.3":{"pli":"Rāgo uppathoti vuccati. ","eng":"Lust is called a deviation, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.76:4.1":{"pli":"Lobho dhammānaṃ paripantho, ","eng":"and greed is a roadblock for skillful qualities. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:4.2":{"pli":"Vayo rattindivakkhayo; ","eng":"Youth is ending day and night. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:4.3":{"pli":"Itthī malaṃ brahmacariyassa, ","eng":"Women are the stain of chastity, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:4.4":{"pli":"Etthāyaṃ sajjate pajā; ","eng":"to which this generation clings. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:4.5":{"pli":"Tapo ca brahmacariyañca, ","eng":"Fervor and chastity ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:4.6":{"pli":"Taṃ sinānamanodakaṃ. ","eng":"are the waterless bath. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.76:5.1":{"pli":"Cha lokasmiṃ chiddāni, ","eng":"There are six holes in the world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:5.2":{"pli":"yattha vittaṃ na tiṭṭhati; ","eng":"where one’s wealth leaks out: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:5.3":{"pli":"Ālasyañca pamādo ca, ","eng":"laziness and negligence, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:5.4":{"pli":"anuṭṭhānaṃ asaṃyamo; ","eng":"lack of initiative and lack of restraint, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Compare the “roadblocks for wealth” at <a href='index.html?q=an10.73#2.2'>AN 10.73:2.2</a>. This shows that <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vitta</i> (“wealth”) is correct here, not <i lang='pi' translate='no'>citta</i> (“mind”). "},"sn1.76:5.5":{"pli":"Niddā tandī ca te chidde, ","eng":"sleepiness and sloth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.76:5.6":{"pli":"sabbaso taṃ vivajjaye”ti. ","eng":"You should completely get rid of these holes!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.77":{"sn1.77:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.77 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.77 ","html":"<article id='sn1.77'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.77:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.77:0.3":{"pli":"Issariyasutta ","eng":"Authority ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.77:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu issariyaṃ loke, ","eng":"“What is authority in the world? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu bhaṇḍānamuttamaṃ; ","eng":"What’s the best of valuables? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu satthamalaṃ loke, ","eng":"What in the world is a rusty sword? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:1.4":{"pli":"kiṃsu lokasmimabbudaṃ. ","eng":"Who is a pest in the world? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"“Pest” is <i lang='pi' translate='no'>abbuda</i>, literally “tumor”, “cancer”. Also an early stage of embryonic development (<a href='index.html?q=sn10.1#3.2'>SN 10.1:3.2</a>) and the name of a hell or a very large number (<a href='index.html?q=snp3.10#8.2'>Snp 3.10:8.2</a>, <a href='index.html?q=sn6.10#6.2'>SN 6.10:6.2</a>). Originally the name of the snake Arbuda crushed beneath Indra’s foot, where he is mentioned along with other foes such as Vritra, Namuci, etc. (Rig Veda 1.51.6, 2.11.20, 2.14.4, 8.3.19, 8.32.3, 8.32.26, 10.67.12). As Arbuda Kādraveya he is, rather curiously, said to have composed Rig Veda 10.94, where he addresses the pressing stones. He is also invoked in Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 13.4.3.9. "},"sn1.77:2.1":{"pli":"Kiṃsu harantaṃ vārenti, ","eng":"Who gets arrested when they take things away? ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:2.2":{"pli":"haranto pana ko piyo; ","eng":"And who is loved when they take things away? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:2.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu punappunāyantaṃ, ","eng":"And who is approved by the astute ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:2.4":{"pli":"abhinandanti paṇḍitā”ti. ","eng":"when they come again and again?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.77:3.1":{"pli":"“Vaso issariyaṃ loke, ","eng":"“Sway is authority in the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:3.2":{"pli":"itthī bhaṇḍānamuttamaṃ; ","eng":"A woman is the best of valuables. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:3.3":{"pli":"Kodho satthamalaṃ loke, ","eng":"Anger in the world is a rusty sword. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:3.4":{"pli":"corā lokasmimabbudā. ","eng":"A bandit is a pest in the world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.77:4.1":{"pli":"Coraṃ harantaṃ vārenti, ","eng":"A bandit gets arrested when they take things away. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:4.2":{"pli":"haranto samaṇo piyo; ","eng":"And an ascetic is loved when they take things away. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:4.3":{"pli":"Samaṇaṃ punappunāyantaṃ, ","eng":"An ascetic is approved by the astute ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.77:4.4":{"pli":"abhinandanti paṇḍitā”ti. ","eng":"when they come again and again.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.78":{"sn1.78:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.78 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.78 ","html":"<article id='sn1.78'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.78:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.78:0.3":{"pli":"Kāmasutta ","eng":"Desire ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.78:1.1":{"pli":"“Kimatthakāmo na dade, ","eng":"“What should one who wants what’s best <j>not give away? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.78:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃ macco na pariccaje; ","eng":"What should a mortal not forsake? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.78:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu muñceyya kalyāṇaṃ, ","eng":"What should be released when it’s good, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.78:1.4":{"pli":"pāpikaṃ na ca mocaye”ti. ","eng":"but not when it’s bad?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.78:2.1":{"pli":"“Attānaṃ na dade poso, ","eng":"“A man shouldn’t give away himself. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The response puns on <i lang='pi' translate='no'>attha</i> (“the goal”, “what’s best”) with <i lang='pi' translate='no'>attā</i>, “oneself”. "},"sn1.78:2.2":{"pli":"attānaṃ na pariccaje; ","eng":"He shouldn’t forsake himself. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.78:2.3":{"pli":"Vācaṃ muñceyya kalyāṇaṃ, ","eng":"Speech should be released when it’s good, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.78:2.4":{"pli":"pāpikañca na mocaye”ti. ","eng":"but not when it’s bad.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.79":{"sn1.79:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.79 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.79 ","html":"<article id='sn1.79'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.79:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.79:0.3":{"pli":"Pātheyyasutta ","eng":"Provisions ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.79:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu bandhati pātheyyaṃ, ","eng":"“What binds the provisions for a journey? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Pātheyya</i> is equivalent to the archaic Latinate <i lang='pi' translate='no'>viatica</i>, “provisions for a journey”. Both this question and the next have the literal sense of safeguarding one’s possessions. "},"sn1.79:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu bhogānamāsayo; ","eng":"What’s the vault of wealth? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Āsaya</i> here has the sense of a place of safety (see Manu 7.160), which for wealth is a “vault”. "},"sn1.79:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu naraṃ parikassati, ","eng":"What drags a person around? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.79:1.4":{"pli":"kiṃsu lokasmi dujjahaṃ; ","eng":"What in the world is hard to give up? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.79:1.5":{"pli":"Kismiṃ baddhā puthū sattā, ","eng":"With what are ordinary beings bound, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.79:1.6":{"pli":"pāsena sakuṇī yathā”ti. ","eng":"like birds in a snare?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.79:2.1":{"pli":"“Saddhā bandhati pātheyyaṃ, ","eng":"“Faith binds the provisions for a journey. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The Buddha elevates the meaning, since faith holds all the factors of the path together. "},"sn1.79:2.2":{"pli":"sirī bhogānamāsayo; ","eng":"Majesty is the vault of wealth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Sirī</i> (“majesty”) is explained by the commentary is <i lang='pi' translate='no'>issariya</i>, “sovereignty”. This suggests that the sense is that wealth can only be safeguarded by power. Alternatively, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>sirī</i> can also mean “luck” or “Lady Luck”, suggesting that the keeping of wealth is just a matter of luck. "},"sn1.79:2.3":{"pli":"Icchā naraṃ parikassati, ","eng":"Desire drags a person around. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.79:2.4":{"pli":"icchā lokasmi dujjahā; ","eng":"Desire in the world is hard to give up. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.79:2.5":{"pli":"Icchābaddhā puthū sattā, ","eng":"Ordinary beings are bound by desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.79:2.6":{"pli":"pāsena sakuṇī yathā”ti. ","eng":"like birds in a snare.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.8":{"sn1.8:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.8 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.8 ","html":"<article id='sn1.8'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.8:0.2":{"pli":"1. Naḷavagga ","eng":"1. A Reed ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.8:0.3":{"pli":"Susammuṭṭhasutta ","eng":"Very Confused ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.8:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn1.8:1.2":{"pli":"Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ","eng":"Standing to one side, that deity spoke this verse in the Buddha’s presence: ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn1.8:2.1":{"pli":"“Yesaṃ dhammā susammuṭṭhā, ","eng":"“Those who are very confused about the teachings ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.8:2.2":{"pli":"paravādesu nīyare; ","eng":"may be led astray by the doctrines of others. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.8:2.3":{"pli":"Suttā te nappabujjhanti, ","eng":"Asleep, they have not woken up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.8:2.4":{"pli":"kālo tesaṃ pabujjhitun”ti. ","eng":"it is time for them to wake!” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.8:3.1":{"pli":"“Yesaṃ dhammā asammuṭṭhā, ","eng":"“Those who are unconfused about the teachings, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.8:3.2":{"pli":"paravādesu na nīyare; ","eng":"won’t be led astray by the doctrines of others. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.8:3.3":{"pli":"Te sambuddhā sammadaññā, ","eng":"They have woken up, they rightly know, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.8:3.4":{"pli":"caranti visame saman”ti. ","eng":"smoothly they walk in the rough.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}},"sn1.80":{"sn1.80:0.1":{"pli":"Saṃyutta Nikāya 1.80 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 1.80 ","html":"<article id='sn1.80'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn1.80:0.2":{"pli":"8. Chetvāvagga ","eng":"8. Slain ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn1.80:0.3":{"pli":"Pajjotasutta ","eng":"Lamp ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn1.80:1.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu lokasmi pajjoto, ","eng":"“What’s the lamp for the world? ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:1.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu lokasmi jāgaro; ","eng":"What in the world is wakeful? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:1.3":{"pli":"Kiṃsu kamme sajīvānaṃ, ","eng":"Who are one’s work colleagues? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:1.4":{"pli":"kimassa iriyāpatho. ","eng":"What is one’s walk of life? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.80:2.1":{"pli":"Kiṃsu alasaṃ analasañca, ","eng":"What nurtures the idle and the tireless, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:2.2":{"pli":"Mātā puttaṃva posati; ","eng":"like a mother her child? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:2.3":{"pli":"Kiṃ bhūtā upajīvanti, ","eng":"By what do the creatures who live off the earth ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:2.4":{"pli":"Ye pāṇā pathavissitā”ti. ","eng":"sustain their life?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.80:3.1":{"pli":"“Paññā lokasmi pajjoto, ","eng":"“Wisdom is the lamp for the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:3.2":{"pli":"sati lokasmi jāgaro; ","eng":"Mindfulness in the world is wakeful. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:3.3":{"pli":"Gāvo kamme sajīvānaṃ, ","eng":"Cattle are one’s work colleagues, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Only the first lines are specifically spiritual, while the remainder is concerned with worldly abundance. "},"sn1.80:3.4":{"pli":"sītassa iriyāpatho. ","eng":"and the furrow is one’s walk of life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"sn1.80:4.1":{"pli":"Vuṭṭhi alasaṃ analasañca, ","eng":"Rain nurtures the idle and the tireless, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:4.2":{"pli":"Mātā puttaṃva posati; ","eng":"like a mother her child. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:4.3":{"pli":"Vuṭṭhiṃ bhūtā upajīvanti, ","eng":"The creatures who live off the earth ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"sn1.80:4.4":{"pli":"Ye pāṇā pathavissitā”ti. ","eng":"sustain their life by rain.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}}}